name: First tag following league/oauth2-server version 4.0.0
body:
### Changelog
- Laravel 5.0.\* support
- Removed create-client command

name: Method Sinature Bugfix
body: The getScope method signature was used in the wrong way.

name: Typo Fix
body: I can't even write JSON properly.

This release is a major rewrite of the package.
It now supports:
league/oauth2-server 4.0.x, PHP 5.4+
and it's built specifically to support Laravel 4.2.

This release breaks compatibility with the previous versions of this library. Do not blindly upgrade.

name: Moving Branches
body: No big changes, only reorganizing the repo

name: Spec conformance.
body: Fixes a bug where the error message isn't formatted according to the oauth spec.

name: Some improvements
body: Solved some issues when choosing a different PDO fetch method.

name: Filter improvements
body: The filter inclusion system has been updated

name: Improved compliance with the OAuth 2 specification
body: fixed a wrong header returned when checking for the access token validity.

name: Bugfixing
body: Fixing #35 where accessTokenValidation wasn't working.

name: Fluent query fixes
body: This release fixes issue #33 where an id different than the one of the client might have been returned by the db query. It also fixes the same problem in other part of the storage interfaces implementations.

name: Security Fixes
body: - Fixes #30 , an issue where wrong IDs might have been returned from the DB.

name: Migrations Improvements
body: Improvement in the migration files. Fixes problem with rollback / reset commands

name: Security Improvements
body: - Fixes a major bug in the password grant type callback

name: Client Metadata and fixes
body: Now there's a client metadata table to add any number of parameters to a client. Remember to run the new migrations.

name: Documentation and improvements in the access token flow
